S'Barclays Mobile Banking app*If you experience problems installing the latest version of Barclays Mobile Banking on HTC One X or Samsung Note 2 handsets, uninstalling and reinstalling the app should fix this*Features\xe2\x80\xa2  Manage your Barclays Personal & Business and Barclaycard Personal accounts on the move \xe2\x80\x93 with the protection of advanced security solutions\xe2\x80\xa2  Check your latest balances\xe2\x80\xa2  View recent transactions & transfer funds between your accounts\xe2\x80\xa2  Make payments to people you\'ve paid before and have put in your payee list\xe2\x80\xa2  Find your nearest Barclays branch or ATM\xe2\x80\xa2  Our log-in process makes access simpler; you\'re automatically protected in the event of\xc2\xa0fraud\xe2\x80\xa2  Now with Mobile PINsentry to make logging into Online Banking easier\xe2\x80\xa2  Get access on up to 3 mobile devices \xe2\x80\xa2 New slider navigation makes Barclays Mobile Banking even easier to usePersonal customers\xe2\x80\xa2  Barclays Mobile Banking is available to sole and joint account holders\xe2\x80\xa2  Barclaycard only accounts cannot be registered to the app \xe2\x80\x93 you\xe2\x80\x99ll need to register your Barclays current account first\xe2\x80\xa2  Manage your Barclays  Personal & Business and Barclaycard Personal accounts in 1 application with 1 secure log-inBusiness customers\xe2\x80\xa2  Barclays Mobile Banking is available to sole signatory Barclays Business current account accounts only. Business & Personal customers can register \xe2\x80\x93 but Barclaycard Business or Corporate  credit cards cannot be registered*Please note that this app does not work on rooted handsets*RegistrationTo register for the Barclays Mobile Banking app, you need to be aged 16 or over and have a UK-registered mobile number and a Barclays current account. You\'ll then need to register your Barclays current account by following the onscreen log-in instructions.You\'ll need your sort code & account number to register. You\xe2\x80\x99ll also need to verify your identity with PINsentry or at a Barclays ATMOnce you\xe2\x80\x99ve registered your current account, your other Barclays Personal and Business accounts (including your Barclaycard Personal accounts) that you view together in Online Banking will be added automatically  and can be viewed and managed in your app. If you have groups of related accounts that  are kept separate online you may need to set up Barclays Mobile Banking on another device for each groupOnce you\'re set up, subsequent log-ins will only require you to have your 5-digit passcode (which you create) to hand.  What\'s more, you don\'t even need to be registered for Barclays Online Banking to register for the Barclays Mobile Banking app.Getting a new phone or  mobile device? There\xe2\x80\x99s no need to re-register or call our helpdesk \xe2\x80\x93 you can set up Barclays  Mobile Banking on up to 3 devices yourself using the appRecent changes:- Sliding menu - New navigation makes everything easier to find  - De-register & re-register - No need to call our helpdesk when you change your phone \xe2\x80\x93 set up Barclays Mobile Banking on up to 3 devices- Barclays Personal & Business accounts - All the accounts you view in Online Banking now shown- Multiple devices now supported- If you are facing issues on navigation, please uncheck "Don\xe2\x80\x99t keep activities". You can find this at Settings > Developer options > APPS > Do NOT keep Activities'
